sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1638003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T25 domain of cyaA from Bordetella pertussis (IPTG inducible)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The T25 domain of CyaA to be used in the bacterial two-hybrid system. The expression of the gene is under control of a lac operator and is induced by IPTG. When protein-coding genes is suffixed to the T25 and T18 domains of the bacterial two-hybrid system, the interaction of these two proteins can be examined. If the protein associates, T25 and T18 associates too, and convert ATP to cAMP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jens Sivk??r Pettersen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: T25 domain
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T25 domain of CyaA from Bordetella pertussis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the T25 domain of the adenylate cyclase, CyaA, from Bordetella pertussis. When associated with the T18 domain of CyaA, the two domains together become active and catalyzes the conversion of ATP to cAMP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jens Sivk??r Pettersen
